    "ts": "2026-03-27T12:50:00+00:00",
    "headline": "Brown-Forman Stock Rises on Merger Talks. Why the Jack Daniel’s Owner Needs a Change.",
    "summary": "Whiskey maker  Brown-Forman  badly needs a change in fortune.  The owner of Jack Daniel’s and Woodford Reserve bourbon confirmed reports Thursday that it is engaged in merger discussions with French liquor giant  Pernod Ricard  The combination would be “akin to a merger of equals,” both companies said.  Pernod had a market capitalization of $18.6 billion entering Thursday, while  Brown-Forman  was valued at $10.8 billion, according to Dow Jones Market Data.",
